message: "If you use SYNAPSE in your work, please cite both the archived software and the paper below."
title: "SYNAPSE: A Multi-LLM Orchestrated AI Tutor for Secure Software Development Education with Neurodivergent-First Design"
abstract: >-
  SYNAPSE is a publicly deployed adaptive tutoring platform for Java programming,
  Python for cybersecurity, and secure software development. It integrates hands-on
  secure-coding exercises with a neurodivergent-first interface and a multi-LLM
  orchestration architecture that coordinates Claude, GPT-4o, and Gemini through the
  Model Context Protocol (MCP), routing interactions by pedagogical intent under a
  three-stage Socratic hint policy. Practical security learning is anchored in
  ShopSecure, a purpose-built deliberately vulnerable web application mapped to six
  OWASP Top 10 (2021) categories.
